{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6f1aab89-1ac9-4bab-b553-628ac2c1873e","content":"No files found in the working directory, so here's the general approach:\n\n## 1. Add `x:DataType` to your XAML\n\nIn `SettingsPage.xaml`, add the CLR namespace and set `x:DataType` on the root element:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='Font size: {0}'}\" />\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThat single `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` attribute is the key change — it tells the XAML compiler the type of the `BindingContext`, enabling **compiled bindings**.\n\n## 2. Catch errors at build time\n\nAdd this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Treat binding failures as build errors -->\n  <MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nWith this enabled, a typo like `{Binding Themee}` produces a **compiler error** instead of silently failing at runtime.\n\n## Key points\n\n- **`x:DataType`** can be set on any element, not just the root — useful when a child binds to a different type (e.g., inside a `DataTemplate`).\n- To **opt out** locally (e.g., for a dynamic binding), use `x:DataType=\"{x:Null}\"`.\n- Compiled bindings are faster at runtime too — they skip reflection-based property resolution.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b06c2dd3-bc75-495d-905a-f57ca864cc06","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The files don't exist in the current directory. The user is asking a general question about how to convert a MAUI page to use compiled bindings. I'll provide the answer directly since there are no files to modify.","outputTokens":563},"id":"bc8ccf22-d80e-480f-b769-3ad2ff35b2c8","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:00:26.002Z","parentId":"bb2316c1-9787-41bf-8dcc-acf1d5f82b4c"}
